name: mkdocs-video
documentation_summary: The HTML text describes the `mkdocs-video` plugin version 1.5.0, released on March 17, 2023, for embedding videos in documentation pages using Markdown syntax. It requires Python version 3.6 or higher and is licensed under the MIT License. The plugin supports various configurations for video display, including autoplay, loop, mute, and controls, and allows for customization of the video tag and CSS styles. It also provides examples of embedding videos from popular services like YouTube, Vimeo, and Facebook Watch. The plugin's global configuration can be overridden on a per-video basis using the Attribute Lists extension.
